wiki.content: "Vulnerable" speaks about the difficulty and fear of being open and vulnerable in a relationship. The lyrics describe the fear of giving too much of oneself to a partner and being hurt or taken advantage of. The artist questions whether her partner is trustworthy enough to handle her vulnerability and provide the necessary emotional support. The song conveys a sense of wanting to be loved and accepted for who she is, flaws and all. The artist admits that opening up and being vulnerable is a risk, but one that she is willing to take in order to have a meaningful, authentic connection with her partner. Ultimately, "Vulnerable" embraces the idea that being emotionally open and honest in a relationship is essential to forging a real connection. The song encourages listeners to be brave and vulnerable in love, even if it means taking a risk and facing the possibility of heartbreak. Read more on Last.fm.
